#!/www/server/panel/pyenv/bin/python3
# coding: utf-8
# =============================================================================
#  Network File System (NFS) — Free Edition
#  Auto-Mount Service Bootstrap
# =============================================================================
#  Description : Lightweight entry point executed by the SysV init script
#                (/etc/init.d/nfs_free) at system boot. Configures the Python
#                module search path, imports nfs_free_main, and calls
#                auto_mount() to mount all NFS shares configured with
#                auto_mount=1 in config/mount.json.
#
#                Failures are silently swallowed because at early boot the
#                NFS configuration may not exist yet (first install) or the
#                remote server may not be reachable. The plugin panel will
#                report mount status on the next dashboard load.
#
#  Invoked by  : /etc/init.d/nfs_free  (via init.sh)
#  Interpreter : /www/server/panel/pyenv/bin/python3  (panel virtualenv)
#                Falls back to /usr/bin/python3 if the virtualenv is absent
#                (handled by init.sh before executing this script).
#
#  Author      : Jose Alexis Correa Valencia (jalexiscv)
